---
import MainLayout from "@layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout
  title="Terms of Service | ExpatDrive"
  description="ExpatDrive terms of service."
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-navy mb-6">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-text-muted mb-8">Last updated: March 3, 2026</p>

    <div class="space-y-6 text-text-primary leading-relaxed">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
      <p>
        By accessing and using ExpatDrive ("the Service"), you agree to these Terms of Service.
        If you do not agree, do not use the Service.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy mt-8">2. Description of Service</h2>
      <p>
        ExpatDrive is a free study tool that helps users prepare for driver's license exams in
        foreign countries. The Service provides practice questions, flashcards, vocabulary drills,
        and informational guides.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy mt-8">3. Disclaimer</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>ExpatDrive is a study aid, not legal advice.</strong> While we strive for accuracy,
        exam content, requirements, fees, and procedures change without notice. Always verify
        current requirements with the relevant government authority before going to the license
        office.
      </p>
      <p>
        ExpatDrive does not guarantee that using the Service will result in passing any exam.
        Results depend on individual study effort and exam conditions.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy mt-8">4. Content Accuracy</h2>
      <p>
        Questions and translations are sourced from official government materials and verified
        to the best of our ability. However, government exams may change at any time.
        If you notice inaccuracies, please <a href="/contact" class="text-navy-light underline hover:text-navy">contact us</a> so we can investigate and update the content.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy mt-8">5. Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p>
        Exam questions are reproduced from publicly available government study materials for
        educational purposes. Translations, explanations, and the study tools themselves are
        the property of CushLabs AI Services.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy mt-8">6. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        The Service is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind. CushLabs AI Services
        shall not be liable for any damages arising from the use or inability to use the Service,
        including but not limited to failure to pass an exam, incorrect information, or
        disruption of study progress.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy mt-8">7. Changes to Terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these terms at any time. Continued use of the Service after changes
        constitutes acceptance of the updated terms.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy mt-8">8. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these terms? Email <a href="mailto:info@cushlabs.ai" class="text-navy-light underline hover:text-navy">info@cushlabs.ai</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</MainLayout>
